reviews.text:
2 weeks - This is a solid flavor. A bit more dragon fruit than I'd like, or better said more pronounced than I'd like. I never was big on dragon fruit at least as a primary element. While the dragon fruit isn't a primary flavor it's definitely noticeable enough. The core strawberry and cream is very solid and worth experimenting with. Definitely a solid flavor overall.&#xD;
&#xD;
At 1 month this really excellent. The dragon fruit has calmed significantly. You can still taste the element right after the strawberry but it’s far more blended in and has less of that dragon fruit bite to it. Nicely creamy and flavorful. Definitely easy to see why this one is popular.&#xD;
&#xD;
Notes - I made this same recipe sans the dragon fruit to see how it would work to build from. After revisiting it at 1 month though I might just try adding some NY cheesecake to it or sweet cream to suit my flavor preferences. Without the dragon fruit it definitely tastes like it's missing something. Another lesson learned, every flavor contributes to the whole and you can't always just axe what you don't like.

This was my first mix. Hated it from the get go. 2 days later I was in love with it. Steeped 12 days and it is still my go to vape flavor. &#xD;
After a month the creams get silky smooth and the taste of stems and plastic are mellowed out a bit.&#xD;
This would be a great recipe with a fruit I could taste right.
